org.lisoft.gonector

Class Move

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.lisoft.gonector.Move

  • public class Move
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents one move as defined by the GTP.

      • PASS

        A special move that should be used when the GoEngine wants to pass.

      • RESIGN

        public static final Move RESIGN
        A special move that should be used when the GoEngine wants to resign.

      • x

        public final int x
        The x (horizontal) position of the move. Will be -1 for special move RESIGN and -2 for special move PASS. The value 0 is to the left and positive numbers to the right. I.e. Cartesian coordinates.

      • y

        public final int y
        The y (vertical) position of the move. The value 0 is to the bottom and positive numbers move up on the board. I.e. Cartesian coordinates.
